      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter alternative</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span><strong> flour</strong> and the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and stir with a wooden spoon for 3-4 min or until a paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682596187181-x200.jpg",
